==Etymology==
Old French conveier (confer French convoyer), Vulgar Latin conviare, from via, "way". Confer "convoy".
===Noun===
*A person or thing that  [[convey]]s, [[transport]]s, [[deliver]]s
*A [[mechanical]] [[arrangement]] for transporting [[material]] or [[object]]s, generally over short or moderate distances, as from one part of a building to another.
*:See also [[conveyor belt]]